    {
      "id": "1lh32g43h",
      "questionNumber": 3,
      "questionText": "<p>From the figure of column chromatography given below, identify incorrect statements.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lh5p0uer/7c946354-9c4a-4c9d-8562-9e055b2cbd1c/125db430-e897-11ed-8179-292e62481b94/file-1lh5p0ues.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lh5p0uer/7c946354-9c4a-4c9d-8562-9e055b2cbd1c/125db430-e897-11ed-8179-292e62481b94/file-1lh5p0ues.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2023 (Online) 6th April Evening Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 123 English\"></p>\n<p>A. Compound 'c' is more polar than 'a' and 'b'</p>\n<p>B. Compound '$$\\mathrm{a}$$' is least polar</p>\n<p>C. Compound 'b' comes out of the column before 'c' and after 'a'</p>\n<p>D. Compound 'a' spends more time in the column</p>\n<p>Choose the correct answer from the options given below:</p>",
      "options": [
        "B and D only",
        "B, C and D only",
        "A, B and D only",
        "A, B and C only"
      ],
      "correctOption": 3,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "purification-of-organic-compounds",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "As the chromatogram, degree of polarity\n$$\n\\rightarrow \\mathrm{a}>\\mathrm{b}>\\mathrm{c} \\text {. }\n$$<br/><br/>\n$\\therefore$ Statements A, B are incorrect as b comes out before ' $C$ ' the statement $C$ is also incorrect.<br/><br/>\nAs a is most polar, it spends most time. Hence, A, B &amp; C are incorrect statements.",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
