    {
      "id": "igT4LNZm5lKrhipeNg9bR",
      "questionNumber": 10,
      "questionText": "The correct decreasing order for acid strength is : ",
      "options": [
        "NO<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>COOH &gt; FCH<sub>2</sub>COOH &gt; CNCH<sub>2</sub>COOH &gt; ClCH<sub>2</sub>COOH",
        "FCH<sub>2</sub>COOH &gt; NCCH<sub>2</sub>COOH &gt; NO<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>COOH &gt; ClCH<sub>2</sub>COOH",
        "CNCH<sub>2</sub>COOH &gt; O<sub>2</sub>NCH<sub>2</sub>COOH &gt; FCH<sub>2</sub>COOH &gt; ClCH<sub>2</sub>COOH",
        "NO<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>COOH &gt; NCCH<sub>2</sub>COOH &gt; FCH<sub>2</sub>COOH &gt; ClCH<sub>2</sub>COOH"
      ],
      "correctOption": 3,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "acid-and-base-strength",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "After releasing proton (H<sup>+</sup>) the more stable anion is more acidic nature. The 4 anions are $$ \\to $$\n<br><br><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/86aMNqDHLNfTLmkcC/9Y4OkBhT7DMaqzNeIaSVFxJZ3s81Q/B51jcEfKXAUVheVtXTbSc0/image.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%;  height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 9th January Morning Slot Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 240 English Explanation\">\n<br><br>Here $$-$$NO<sub>2</sub>, $$-$$ CN, $$-$$Cl, $$-$$F all of them have $$-$$ I effective and all have same distance from the anion ($$-$$ O<sup>$$-$$</sup>).\n<br><br>So depending on which one have more power $$-$$ I effect will be more stable. \n<br><br>Acidic nature $$ \\propto $$ $$-$$ I power.\n<br><br>$$-$$ I power order : \n<br><br>$$-$$ NO<sub>2</sub> &gt; $$-$$ C $$ \\equiv $$ N &gt; $$-$$ F &gt; $$-$$ Cl\n<br><br>So, acidic strength order $$ \\to $$\n<br><br>NO<sub>2</sub> $$-$$ CH<sub>2</sub> $$-$$ COOH &gt; NC $$-$$ CH<sub>2</sub> $$-$$ COOH\n<br>&gt; F $$-$$ CH<sub>2</sub> $$-$$ COOH &gt; Cl $$-$$ CH<sub>2</sub> $$-$$ COOH",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
